{
  "stem": "33.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I think her family was the richest.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Probably they had a big candy factory, and I guess they were the richest among us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the rest of us, for awhile, we thought that maybe we cannot go to school anymore.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when you're raised with the importance of learning all your life, and there you are, you're just turning 14, and maybe you can't go to school anymore, it is pretty traumatic.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Even though, in retrospect, compared to what awaited us, it was no big deal.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But again, I was a good student, and my-- my family knew people in our community.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I did get in a public high school as one of five Jewish girls.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Actually, the first year, it was a Protestant school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then it was taken over by a public high school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in subsequent years, there were no more Jews admitted.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So it was us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were five Jewish girls, and there were two Jewish boys in a parallel class.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't have co-ed classes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no-- as of 1941, there were no more Jewish kids admitted.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we were it in a student body of 400 some students.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the 40's, of course, the war was already raging all around us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the refugees from Poland, Jewish people who managed to escape, came frequently to my parents' house.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Or sometimes, we went out to the trains.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we-- I remember going with my mother and taking food for the refugees.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But people who came to the house, they also were asking for food, or clothes, or financial assistance, what have you.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they started to tell us about the ghettos and about concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
